parameters: I was raised in an orphanage.

Originally, I joined the hero party to send the money I
earned back to the orphanage to support everyone's living.

But that was exploited, and I was trapped by the woman in
the video, Bellra.

Rise was called out on a quest to subdue a super-sized
monster.

However, that request was a trap to isolate and divide Rise.
What awaited her was not a monster but a woman who called
herself Bellra.
"Ufufu, these kids are really cute, aren't they?"

Surrounding Bellra were the girls from the orphanage where
Rise grew up.

They weren't tied up with rope, but it was clear they
couldn't move, likely under some sort of hypnosis even if
not fully brainwashed.

"You... If you lay even one finger on those kids, I'll send
you flying!!"

"No need to glare like that. If you sign a slave contract
with me, I won't be able to touch them, you know?"
The children looked at Rise with anxious faces.

"I've explained about the slave contract, haven't I? If you
sign it, I can't harm these kids."

"Yes, I heard you loud and clear. Including the part where
you plan to completely brainwash me."

"Ufufu, all you have to do is not break until your friends
come to rescue you."
"You believe in them, don't you? Your friends?"

Come on, hurry up and sign the slave contract. Bellra pulled
one of the hostage children closer and flashed a knife.

"Oh? You don't really think a bad adult would do something
so heroic, do you?"

"I've gathered the children that Rise-chan wanted to see,
especially those she was close with. You should be
grateful."
Grinding her teeth, Rise glared at Bellra.

"It's not like I specifically targeted you. Any girl from
the Hero Party would have been fine at first."

"But you know, as I gathered information, it turned out that
your weaknesses were the most apparent."

"Besides, there's someone who took a liking to you and
insisted on wanting to train you."

"Fufu, well, that person was also the one who told me all
about you."
With a smile, she said, "You're quite popular, aren't you?"

"What's that supposed to mean? And did you just say 'at
first'?"

"Does that mean you plan to target my other companions after
me?!"

"Yes, that's right. I'll extract information about your
other companions from you and use it to figure out how to
brainwash them."

"Even though it's called a slave contract, there are various
methods, from direct to indirect."

"For example, Tina-chan's Full Body, was it? No matter how
ancient the technique, to bypass that skill and apply a
slave contract..."

"I need to hear about its specifics in detail and improve
the technique to exploit the skill's weaknesses."

Bellra lightly winked as she said, "That's the kind of
information I want you to tell me."

"So come on, let's quickly form a contract of servitude,
shall we?"

"As if I could just nod and say 'yes' after hearing all
that!!"

Bellra, without any hesitation, stabs a knife into the hand
of a nearby child.

"It hurts, doesn't it? But it's all because Rise Onee-san
won't listen to me. It's all Rise Onee-san's fault, you
know?"

As Rise approaches, Bellra thrusts the knife against the
child's neck to restrain her.

"Now, what will you do? Next, I'll target this child's neck,
and after that, another child will suffer. What's it going
to be?"

The captured child screams and cries. The initial stabbing
in the hand was done to make her cry and cloud Rise's
judgment.

"Oh? Don't you feel sorry for the children? Maybe next I
should tear off your breasts."

Hearing the screams, Rise murmurs softly while clenching her
hands so tightly that her nails dig in and draw blood.

"Hmph, just remember this. Even if you brainwash me, the
members of Lucent... they will never lose to someone like
you."

"You were once a part of the hero's party, and now you've
become a slave so easily. Your words don't carry much
weight."

Rise shows a frustrated expression at Bellra's words, but
still, there's a determined strength in the depths of her
eyes.

"I will not break, no matter what happens. I won't be
brainwashed."

"I don't know if it's revenge or something else, but you'll
regret targeting the members of the hero's party."

Upon hearing those words, Bellra shows a surprised
expression for the first time with an "Eh?"

"Huh? I don't have any particular grudge against the hero's
party."

The words that came out of Bellra's mouth were unexpected
for Rise.

"The women of the hero's party are quite rare, and they're
all cute, right? I thought they might be worth some money,
that's half the reason."

"The other half is just curiosity about how much the hero's
party is really worth, so I thought I'd play around a bit."
But well, she twists her mouth.

"Since it's all just a game, it would be more interesting if
there was some resistance."

"Ufufu, that's right. If I'm going to break up the hero
members, it would be fun to infiltrate and crush from within
the country, like a surprise."

"There's a human trafficking organization I was thinking of
discarding anyway. Maybe I'll show them a little tail on
purpose."
"But before that? I have to sell off Rise-chan, don't I?"

Bellra: "Ufufu, Rise-chan. Do your best to endure wherever
you're sold off to, okay?"

Rise (That's right. I was forced into a contract of
servitude by this woman named Bellra.)

Rise (Then I was knocked unconscious, and when I regained
consciousness, I was in that dark room.)

"Yes, the woman in Selphie's video, that Bellra person, she
forced me into a contract of servitude."

Rise began to recount everything from the fake subjugation
request, to Bellra, and then about Nolz.
While trembling with anger, Suelle listened to Rise's story.
"I can't forgive it either... my own incompetence as well."

She must have spilled information about her companions. Rise
had a pained expression on her face.

"It can't be helped under those circumstances. More
importantly, let's focus on rescuing our companions now."

Suelle felt it was better to have a goal rather than to
comfort Rise right now.
That's how desperate Rise seemed to be.
Rise slapped her cheeks to psych herself up.
"Thanks to what I remembered, I've found a clue."

"Nolz. This man was deeply connected to a human trafficking
organization."

"Which means if we catch him, we should be able to get
information."
"I see, but if we don't know where he is..."

"That's not a problem. He's called me to a certain place
several times under the pretext of 'routine maintenance'."

"It seems he was planning to call me again soon, so we'll
use this opportunity to storm in."

"Understood. He's the one who put Rise through such an
ordeal. We'll definitely capture him and make him spill
everything about Tina and Selphie."

"Of course. The place is accessible through an underground
passage from the orphanage where I was, so let's head to the
orphanage first."

The destination \C[2]Nolz Orphanage\C[0] has been added to
the map.
